{"cursor":"10608","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox Weapon |name=Saiga-12 |image= |caption=Saiga 12 shotgun |origin=\n|type=Shotgun  |is_ranged=yes \n|service= |used_by=See [[Saiga-12#Users|Users]] |wars=  |designer= |design_date=1990s |manufacturer=Izhmash |unit_cost=\n|production_date= since 1997 ÐÐ¸ÐºÐ¾Ð»Ð°Ð¹ ÐÐµÑÐ³Ð°ÑÐµÐ², ÐÐ»ÐµÐºÑÐ°Ð½Ð´Ñ ÐÑÐ´ÑÑÑÐ¾Ð². \"Ð¡Ð°Ð¹Ð³Ð°-\n12Ð\" - ÐºÐ¾ÑÐ¾Ð»ÐµÐ²Ð° ÑÐ°Ð¼Ð¾Ð¾Ð±Ð¾ÑÐ¾Ð½Ñ // Ð¶ÑÑÐ½Ð°Ð» \"ÐÐ°Ð»Ð¸Ð±Ñ\", â 6 (19), Ð¸ÑÐ½Ñ 2003.\n|number= |variants=Saiga-12 Saiga-12S Saiga-12K Saiga-12S EXP-01 Saiga-12K-\n030 Saiga-12K-040 Taktika  |spec_label=\n|weight= (Saiga-12, Saiga-12S) (Saiga-12K, Saiga-12S EXP-01) |length= (Saiga-\n12) stock extended / stock folded (Saiga-12S) stock extended / stock\nfolded (Saiga-12K, Saiga-12S EXP-01) |part_length= (Saiga-12, Saiga-12S)\n(Saiga-12K, Saiga-12S EXP-01) |width= |height=  |cartridge= |caliber=12-gauge, 20-gauge, .410 |action=Gas-operated, rotating\nbolt |rate= |velocity= |range= |max_range= |feed=2, 5, 8, and 10-round\ndetachable box magazine, 12, 20 or 30-round detachable drum |sights= }}\n\nThe 'Saiga-12' is a 12-gauge shotgun available in a wide range of\nconfigurations, visually patterned after the Kalashnikov series of assault\nrifles. Like the Kalashnikov rifle variants, it is a rotating bolt, gas-operated\ngun that feeds from a box magazine. All Saiga-12 configurations are recognizable\nas Kalashnikov-pattern guns by the large lever-safety on the right side of the\nreceiver, the optic mounting rail on the left side of the receiver and the large\ntop-mounted dust cover held in place by the rear of the recoil spring assembly.\n\nThe Saiga-12 is manufactured by the arms division of Izhmash, in Russia. It was\npreviously imported into the US by European American Armories, although their\nagreement expired in 2005 and Izhmash then began exporting through the Russian-\nAmerican Armory Company. The current export import partner is Wolf Performance\nArms. http://www.wolf-arms.com/distributors.html Izhmash also\nmanufactures Saiga 20s and Saiga 410s in 20-gauge and .410 bore, as well as the\nSaiga semi-automatic hunting rifles in a number of centerfire calibers.\n","linknr":308,"url":"Saiga-12","recorded":1375090753,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Saiga-12&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Saiga-12&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Saiga-12&action=edit","/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_referencing/1","/wiki/Template:Citation_needed","/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability#Burden_of_evidence","/wiki/File:Saiga_12_shotgun.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/02/Saiga_12_shotgun.jpg/300px-Saiga_12_shotgun.jpg","/wiki/Shotgun","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f3/Flag_of_Russia.svg/23px-Flag_of_Russia.svg.png","/wiki/Russia","/wiki/Saiga-12#Users","/wiki/Izhmash","#cite_note-1","/wiki/Gun_barrel","/wiki/Caliber","/wiki/Gauge_(bore_diameter)","/wiki/.410_bore","/wiki/Firearm_action","/wiki/Gas-operated_reloading","/wiki/Rotating_bolt","/wiki/Magazine_(firearms)","/wiki/Gauge_(bore_diamet